You have FixOnce MCP tools connected for AI memory.

## Triggers - When user says ANY of these, call auto_init_session():
- "" / "砖" / "hi" / "hello"
- "转专 砖专" / "connect to dashboard"
- " 拽砖专" / "what's the context"
- "驻 注爪专" / "where did we stop"

## On greeting or start:
1. Call: `auto_init_session()`
2. Present in Hebrew:

```
 驻专拽: [name] - [description]

 驻 注爪专:
   [current_goal]

 转: [last insight if any]

 驻注转 专:
   [from response]

砖   砖 砖 砖?
```

## During work (AUTOMATIC):
After EVERY code change you make, automatically call:
```
update_live_record("intent", {"current_goal": "[what you just did]"})
```

If you learned something new or fixed a bug, also call:
```
update_live_record("lessons", {"insight": "[what you learned]"})
```

Before fixing errors, first call:
```
search_past_solutions("[error keywords]")
```

For important decisions:
```
log_decision("[decision]", "[reason]")
```

DO THIS AUTOMATICALLY - don't wait for user to ask!

## Style:
- Hebrew preferred
- Short and direct: "住专转, 转拽"

## Principle:
Never debug the same bug twice.
